Jude Fawley is a young man from Marygreen who dreams of studying at Christminster but becomes a stone mason instead.
Susanna Bridehead is Jude's cousin. She is unconventional in her beliefs and education, but marries the schoolmaster Richard Phillotson.
Arabella Donn is Jude's first wife. She enjoys spending time in bars and in the company of men.
Aunt Drusilla is the relative who raised Jude.
Richard Phillotson is the schoolmaster who first introduces Jude to the idea of studying at the university. He later marries Sue.
Little Father Time (Little Jude) is Jude and Arabella's son, raised in Australia by Arabella's parents. He is said to have the mind of an old man, though he is a young child.